THE PILOT MADE THE LNDG APPROACH WITH FULL FLAPS AT AN AIRSPEED OF APPROXIMATELY 90 KTS. 
ACCORDING TO THE PILOT, HE ENCOUNTERED WIND SHEAR AT THE RUNWAY THRESHOLD, 
LANDED HARD, AND BOUNCED SEVERAL TIMES. THE LANDING GEAR COLLAPSED. 
THE PILOT TRIED TO MAKE A GO-AROUND BUT WAS UNABLE TO CLIMB OUT OF 
GROUND EFFECT OR GAIN FLYING SPEED. THE AIRCRAFT STALLED AND COLLIDED WITH 
THE GROUND LEFT OF THE RUNWAY. RUNWAY 26 WAS USED. THE LOCAL WINDS WERE 
REPORTED AT 260 DEGS AT 5 KTS. 
THE PILOT LANDED HARD AND COLLAPSED THE LANDING GEAR WHEN HE FAILED 
TO ARREST HIS DESCENT RATE DURING LANDING. AFTERWARDAS HE TRIED TO 
MAKE A GO-AROUND THE PILOT DID NOT OBTAIN ADEQUATE FLYING SPEED, THE 
AIRCRAFT STALLED AND COLLIDED WITH THE GROUND. 
